
JS Basic Events
----------------

. Click (onClick)
. Double Click (ondblclick)
. Right Click (oncontextmenu)

. Mouse Hover (onmouseenter)
. Mouse Out (onmouseout)
. Mouse Down (onmousedown)
. Mouse up(onmouseup)

. Key Press (onkeypress)
. Key Up (onkeyup)

. Load(onload)
. Unload (onunload)

Define Events
_------------

1. Adding events in HTML inline.
 <button onClick="myFunc()">Click me</button>

2. From JS events
  
  element.onclick = myFunc;

3. From JS addEventListner method

  element.addEventListner("click", myFunc); 

  Examples
  ========
//HTML
  <button id="btn" onclick="myFunc()">click me</button>

  //javascript

  function myFunc() {
    consnole.log("Hello, Good Evening");
  }